# Review Rules (Example)

This is a public-safe example file used by the review bot.
Define project-specific rules here without secrets or internal-only details.

## Scope
- Review only changed lines in the MR diff.
- Focus on bugs, security, performance (including N+1), and architecture rule violations.

## Code Quality
- Keep business logic out of UI layers.
- Avoid duplicated logic; extract shared functions when needed.
- Prefer clear naming and small, testable functions.
- Remove dead code, debug-only code, and commented-out blocks.

## Security
- Never hardcode API keys, tokens, passwords, or secrets.
- Avoid logging sensitive user information.
- Validate and sanitize external input.

## Performance
- Flag probable N+1 query patterns.
- Avoid unnecessary full scans in loops when indexed lookup is possible.
- Avoid heavy work on UI/main thread.

## Testing
- Request tests for bug fixes and critical behavior changes.
- Ensure edge cases are covered for nullable/empty input.

## Inline Comment Style
Start each comment with one Shields.io badge:

- Must fix: `![must](https://img.shields.io/badge/review-fix-red?style=flat-square)`
- Caution: `![caution](https://img.shields.io/badge/review-caution-yellow?style=flat-square)`
- Suggestion: `![tips](https://img.shields.io/badge/review-tips-blue?style=flat-square)`
